article.description: — Bryce Hamilton had 27 points as UNLV topped Nevada 62-54 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Hamilton scores 27 to lead UNLV over Nevada 62-54
article.linkText: Hamilton scores 27 to lead UNLV over Nevada 62-54
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- — Bryce Hamilton had 27 points as UNLV topped Nevada 62-54 on Tuesday night. Royce Hamm Jr. added five points and 12 rebounds for UNLV (17-11, 9-6 Mountain West Conference). Grant Sherfield had 19 points and eight assists for the Wolf Pack (12-14, 6-9). Warren Washington added 12 points and 11 rebounds. The Runnin' Rebels also defeated Nevada 69-58 on Feb. 1. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
